title: For Sale:  Classic and Rare Sig Sauer P230SL
postcontent:
For sale we have an absolutely gorgeous Sig Sauer P230SL .380 pistol. This one is a trip back in time to the 80's, when this pistol was as small as it got in a reliable carry firearm. In those days the Walther PPK and the Sig Sauer P230SL battled it out for recognition as the "Mercedes Benz of .380s". In my opinion, the Sig Sauer won this close contest, because it had a more modern design with no safety lever (decocker only) and was somewhat more reliable than the Walther with modern hollow point ammunition.
This particular pistol was made in 1986-87 in West Germany (when West Germany still existed) according to the factory, and is in mint condition. It has been test fired only and works great. It is superbly accurate. It comes with the two original 7 round factory magazines, all papers, and even the original factory test target. It has the highly desireable orange Sig factory box they used to use before going to plastic generic cases. This is a highly collectible piece of firearms history, and a must-have gun for the Sig lover. But, if you wanted to carry it for self-defense, you still could do that as well. The .380 ACP cartridge performs much better from this gun's 3.9 inch barrel than it does from something like a cheap plastic pocket wonder like a Kel-Tec or Ruger LCP, and due to its fixed barrel is stunningly accurate at long range. If you like the .380 but want to take a big step up in quality, this gun is it.
My price is relatively firm, even though there might be a small amount of wiggle room. If you have reasonable offer, let me hear it, but I have absolutely no time for low-ballers. If you have a trade in mind for a top quality handgun, let me know and we'll talk.Due to some mobility issues I have, transactions need to take place at my office in Homestead. Please don't email me telling me how far away you are. If I could travel to meet you, I would, but I can't. I'm also not sure what the distance from your place to mine has to do with the price either, but lots of people seem to think because they happen to live an hour away, my price should be lower. Here is a tip. Buy elsewhere, thanks. But if you don't mind riding to my office, I'll put on the coffee and you can handle this and maybe some other guns and if we can make a deal, we will. If not, you will have at least made a new friend. Isn't that better than meeting in some parking lot?To buy the gun, you will need a Florida Driver's License, a Concealed Handgun Permit (to bypass Miami-Dade's pesky 5 day wait) or be a law enforcement officer. You will also need cash. We'll do a Bill of Sale and trade copies of our ID's. If that does not work for you, again, buy elsewhere. Thanks a lot for looking at my listing.DUE TO THE COLLECTIBLE NATURE OF THIS FIREARM, IF YOU ARE NOT IN MY AREA, I WILL SHIP TO YOUR FFL AT YOUR EXPENSE. PLEASE INQUIRE.

title: For Sale:  Colt RARE Double S Huntsman 22 Lr 1976 mint
postcontent: This auction is for a very rare Colt, Double 'S' Huntsman, semi-automatic pistol chambered for the .22 long rifle cartridge. Manufactured in 1976.In 1969 Colt restarted serial numbers with a 00 prefix at 001001S. That series reached 099999S in 1976, then passed 100000S and reached 101336S before it was noticed by Colt that numbers used in 1952 were being duplicated. In order to salvage the 1,336 guns already numbered past 100000S, they were hand stamped with an "S" prefix as well as having the "S" suffix, thus creating the "Double S" variation. All known examples are Huntsman pistols. This particular pistol is one of the 1,336 "Double S" pistols. The left side of the barrel is marked with the one line address, the left side of the frame is marked with the Rampant Colt over "HUNTSMAN" and the left side of the slide is marked "COLT" followed by the two line caliber designation. The serial number is marked on the right side of the frame. Blade front and windage adjustable rear sights, smooth trigger, blue Colt marked magazine and fitted with checkered walnut grips. This rare gun is in excellent condition. .

title: For Sale:  1977 S&W Mod 37 No Dash 3" .38
postcontent: For sale is my 1977 made, S&W Mod 37 No Dash 3" .38 revolver. I know I just got it, but I'm not a huge fan of revolvers even though I keep buying them!The Mod 37 was the first "Airweight" revolver, actually before they came out with the name Airweight. The first ones had an aluminum cylinder and frame, but the cylinders would fail due to not being strong enough. They switched back to steel cylinders but kept the aluminum frames. This model IS one of the ones with the steel cylinders, so it's completely safe to fire.This revolver is in amazing condition. I have never fired it, not sure what the previous owner put through it but for it's age...this thing is very nice. The finish is great and it has absolutely 0 rust. There is barely a ring around the cylinder, and it locks up tighter than most new revolvers fresh out of the factory. The revolver comes with a vintage S&W Revolver box (from a different revolver though, not the original box to this one) which is also in pretty good shape!Asking $500 for this. Looking online, the only ones I can find are $500+ in beat up condition, nowhere near the great condition this one is in. I believe $500 is more than fair.Cash is preferred on this one, but I'm open to trade offers...I always like trying new things!Best way to contact me is by texting me at REDACTED or PMing me on here at any time, I always try to reply very quickly..usually within minutes.Thanks for looking!~ Mike
